---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Header from "../components/sections/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/sections/Footer.astro";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="dark" class="dark">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title="The Inner Circle | Order of the 19th" description="The Master and the Two Nines: 19 members who hold the Order's deepest knowledge across five centuries" />
    <style>
      .member-id {
        font-family: 'Courier New', 'Monaco', Consolas, monospace;
        font-weight: 400;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        padding: 0.375rem 0.875rem;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(184, 134, 11, 0.12) 0%, rgba(184, 134, 11, 0.06) 100%);
        border: 2px solid rgba(184, 134, 11, 0.35);
        border-radius: 0.5rem;
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.25rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
        text-align: center;
        box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(184, 134, 11, 0.15);
        transition: all 0.2s ease;
        position: relative;
      }
      
      .member-id::before {
        content: "◈";
        font-size: 0.65rem;
        color: #B8860B;
        opacity: 0.7;
        margin-right: 0.15rem;
      }
      
      .member-id.front-nine::before {
        content: "◆";
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        color: #B8860B;
        opacity: 0.8;
      }
      
      .member-id.back-nine::before {
        content: "◇";
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        color: #B8860B;
        opacity: 0.8;
      }
      
      .member-id:hover {
        border-color: rgba(184, 134, 11, 0.5);
        box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(184, 134, 11, 0.25);
        transform: translateY(-1px);
      }
      
      .member-id-hero {
        font-size: 1rem;
        padding: 0.5rem 1.25rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.15em;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(218, 165, 32, 0.2) 0%, rgba(184, 134, 11, 0.15) 100%);
        border: 2.5px solid rgba(218, 165, 32, 0.5);
        box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(218, 165, 32, 0.3), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }
      
      .member-id-hero::before {
        content: "✦";
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        color: #DAA520;
        opacity: 0.9;
      }
      
      .member-id-hero .roman {
        color: #DAA520;
        font-weight: 800;
        text-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(218, 165, 32, 0.3);
      }
      
      .member-id .roman {
        font-weight: 800;
        color: #B8860B;
        text-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(184, 134, 11, 0.3);
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      }
      
      .member-id .separator {
        color: rgba(184, 134, 11, 0.5);
        font-weight: 400;
      }
      
      .member-id .number {
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      
      .member-note {
        font-size: 0.875rem;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
        margin-top: 1rem;
        text-align: center;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-12">
      
      <!-- Page Header -->
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 text-[color:var(--accent)]">
          The Inner Circle
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-[color:var(--color-text)] max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          Nineteen members hold the deepest knowledge of the Order. Led by The Master, 
          they are divided as golf divides its course: the Front 9 who carried the 
          tradition through shadow, and the Back 9 who bring it into light.
        </p>
      </div>

 <!-- THE MASTER - Hero Section -->
<section class="mb-20 text-center">
  <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6 text-[color:var(--accent)]">
    The Master
  </h2>
  <p class="text-lg mb-12 text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    Our eternal founder, whose vision and passion laid the foundation for all who follow
  </p>
  
  <a href="/members/master-liang" class="block max-w-2xl mx-auto bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-8 hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow hover:border-[color:var(--accent)] no-underline">
  <div class="w-48 h-48 mx-auto mb-6 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
    <img src="/images/man1800.png" alt="Master Liang" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
  </div>
  
  <div class="member-id member-id-hero"><span class="roman">I</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">1</span></div>
  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Master Liang</h2>
  <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-4">St Andrews, Scotland • 1524–1590</p>
  <p class="text-lg mb-4 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ Old Course at St Andrews</p>
  
  <blockquote class="text-xl italic my-6 px-4 border-l-4 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
    "I served drinks before I served wisdom."
  </blockquote>
  
  <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-6">
    In his late twenties, Master Liang pushed a humble food cart to the edge of the Old Course
    and quietly turned thirsty golfers into the first members of an invisible club.
  </p>
  
  <span class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-[color:var(--accent)] !text-white rounded-md hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity">
    Read His Legend →
  </span>
</a>

  </div>
</section>


      <!-- THE FRONT NINE -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-[color:var(--accent)]">The Front Nine</h2>
          <p class="text-xl text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            Legends Who Shaped the Game
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <!-- Member 1 -->
         <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
          <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
            <img src="/images/man1950.png" alt="Brother MacLaing" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="member-id front-nine"><span class="roman">I</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">3</span></div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Brother MacLaing</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">St Andrews, Scotland • c. 1720–1779</p>
          <p class="text-sm mb-3 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ Leith Links</p>
          <blockquote class="text-sm italic my-4 px-3 border-l-2 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
            "A round is not finished until a man has shared it in good company."
          </blockquote>
          <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-4">
            A quiet trader’s son who carried Master Liang’s family custom east to Leith, Brother MacLaing became the discreet bridge between taverns, new clubs and those who chose to finish their round properly at an unseen 19th.
          </p>
       <a href="/members/brother-maclaing" class="block bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all hover:border-[color:var(--accent)] no-underline">
  <!-- content -->
  <span class="text-[color:var(--accent)] hover:underline text-sm">Read Their Legend →</span>
</a>

        </div>

          <!-- Member 2 -->
          <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
            <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
              <img src="/images/man1950.png" alt="Brother Calder" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <div class="member-id front-nine"><span class="roman">I</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">5</span></div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Brother Calder</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">St Andrews, Scotland • c. 1714–1781</p>
            <p class="text-sm mb-3 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ The Old Course, St Andrews</p>
            <blockquote class="text-sm italic my-4 px-3 border-l-2 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
              "Eighteen holes mark the score, but the nineteenth reveals the player."
            </blockquote>
            <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-4">
              Fascinated by how golfers moved across the Old Course and gathered after play, Brother Calder stood witness when it was cut to eighteen holes and began sketching a hidden nineteenth in his mind – a brotherhood without walls for those who stayed to share the day.
            </p>
           <a href="/members/brother-calder" class="block bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all hover:border-[color:var(--accent)] no-underline">
  <!-- content -->
  <span class="text-[color:var(--accent)] hover:underline text-sm">Read Their Legend →</span>
</a>

          </div>

          <!-- Member 3 -->
          <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
            <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
              <img src="/images/man1950.png" alt="Brother Rowan" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <div class="member-id front-nine"><span class="roman">II</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">12</span></div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Brother Rowan</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">Edinburgh, Scotland • c. 1768–1836</p>
            <p class="text-sm mb-3 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ Bruntsfield Links & Musselburgh Links</p>
            <blockquote class="text-sm italic my-4 px-3 border-l-2 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
              "Wherever a golfer ends his day, there should be one door that opens a little easier for him."
            </blockquote>
            <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-4">
              A commercial traveller with a modest game but an excellent memory, Brother Rowan carried the quiet customs of MacLaing and Calder out of St Andrews and Leith and into the taverns and golf houses of Edinburgh and Musselburgh, recruiting innkeepers into an informal nineteenth‑hole network of stories, favours and information.
            </p>
           <a href="/members/brother-rowan" class="block bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all hover:border-[color:var(--accent)] no-underline">
  <!-- content -->
  <span class="text-[color:var(--accent)] hover:underline text-sm">Read Their Legend →</span>
</a>

          </div>

          <!-- Member 4 -->
          <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
            <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
              <img src="/images/lady1950.png" alt="Sister Morag Fisher" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <div class="member-id front-nine"><span class="roman">II</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">7</span></div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Sister Morag</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">Fisherrow, Musselburgh • c. 1778–1842</p>
            <p class="text-sm mb-3 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ Musselburgh Links</p>
            <blockquote class="text-sm italic my-4 px-3 border-l-2 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
              "I carried fish and stories on the same back, and both found good tables in the end."
            </blockquote>
            <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-4">
              A formidable Musselburgh fishwife who played golf on her days off and walked miles with a creel on her back, Sister Morag became the first woman of the Order, carrying its spirit along the coast in the gossip and trade of the fishing boats and binding the nineteenth hole to smoky kitchens, harbour taverns and the rough laughter of her own.
            </p>
          <a href="/members/sister-morag" class="block bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all hover:border-[color:var(--accent)] no-underline">
  <!-- content -->
  <span class="text-[color:var(--accent)] hover:underline text-sm">Read Their Legend →</span>
</a>

           </div>

            <!-- Member 5 -->
            <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
              <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                <img src="/images/man1950.png" alt="Brother Shaw" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
              </div>
              <div class="member-id front-nine"><span class="roman">I</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">2</span></div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Brother Shaw</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">Greenwich, England • c. 1575–1645</p>
              <p class="text-sm mb-3 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ Royal Blackheath Golf Club</p>
              <blockquote class="text-sm italic my-4 px-3 border-l-2 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
                "A game without a gathering is only half played."
              </blockquote>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-4">
                A river man moving between Greenwich taverns and the royal ground on the heath, Brother Shaw carried the quiet customs of the 19th hole from Scottish links into England’s first true golfing society, ensuring every round above London ended within sight of the Thames.
              </p>
          <a href="/members/brother-shaw" class="block bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all hover:border-[color:var(--accent)] no-underline">
  <!-- content -->
  <span class="text-[color:var(--accent)] hover:underline text-sm">Read Their Legend →</span>
</a>

            </div>

            <!-- Member 6 -->
            <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
              <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                <img src="/images/man1950.png" alt="Brother Cartwright" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
              </div>
              <div class="member-id front-nine"><span class="roman">V</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">19</span></div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Brother Cartwright</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">Blackwall & Calcutta • c. 1790–1860</p>
              <p class="text-sm mb-3 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ Calcutta Golfing Society</p>
              <blockquote class="text-sm italic my-4 px-3 border-l-2 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
                "Wherever a ship can carry a ball and a bottle, the 19th hole will follow."
              </blockquote>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-4">
                Born among the masts of the East India Docks and later a clerk on the route to India, Brother Cartwright turned dockside inns and Calcutta verandas into true 19th holes, stitching the Order’s river‑born traditions into the growing game across the empire.
              </p>
            <a href="/members/brother-cartwright" class="block bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all hover:border-[color:var(--accent)] no-underline">
  <!-- content -->
  <span class="text-[color:var(--accent)] hover:underline text-sm">Read Their Legend →</span>
</a>

            </div>

            <!-- Member 7 -->
            <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
              <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                <img src="/images/man1950.png" alt="Brother O'Donnell" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
              </div>
              <div class="member-id front-nine"><span class="roman">V</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">34</span></div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Brother O'Donnell</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">New York & Long Island, USA • 1895–1970</p>
              <p class="text-sm mb-3 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ Shinnecock Hills Golf Club</p>
              <blockquote class="text-sm italic my-4 px-3 border-l-2 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
                "In America, everything grows faster – even the stories after the round."
              </blockquote>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-4">
                An Irish-American hotelier who made his Long Island bar the unofficial 19th hole for travelling pros, Wall Street men and caddies, Brother O'Donnell translated the Order's quiet customs into the loud new world of American golf and big-money majors.
              </p>
            <a href="/members/brother-odonnell" class="block bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all hover:border-[color:var(--accent)] no-underline">
  <!-- content -->
  <span class="text-[color:var(--accent)] hover:underline text-sm">Read Their Legend →</span>
</a>

            </div>

            <!-- Member 8 -->
            <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
              <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                <img src="/images/man1950.png" alt="Brother Nakamura" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
              </div>
              <div class="member-id front-nine"><span class="roman">XII</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">58</span></div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Brother Nakamura</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">Kobe & Shanghai • 1910–1988</p>
              <p class="text-sm mb-3 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ Kasumigaseki Country Club</p>
              <blockquote class="text-sm italic my-4 px-3 border-l-2 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
                "Empires rise and fall; a shared drink after a round endures."
              </blockquote>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-4">
                A shipping agent who moved between Kobe and Shanghai through war, occupation and reopening, Brother Nakamura quietly maintained 19th-hole sanctuaries for diplomats, traders and caddies, ensuring the Order survived every ban and boom in East Asia.
              </p>
            <a href="/members/brother-nakamura" class="block bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all hover:border-[color:var(--accent)] no-underline">
  <!-- content -->
  <span class="text-[color:var(--accent)] hover:underline text-sm">Read Their Legend →</span>
</a>

            </div>

            <!-- Member 9 -->
            <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
              <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                <img src="/images/man1950.png" alt="Brother Devereux" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
              </div>
              <div class="member-id front-nine"><span class="roman">XVII</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">147</span></div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Brother Devereux</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">London & Global • 1940–2005</p>
              <p class="text-sm mb-3 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ Royal St George's</p>
              <blockquote class="text-sm italic my-4 px-3 border-l-2 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
                "If we do not tend our stories, someone else will rewrite them."
              </blockquote>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-4">
                A peripatetic lawyer-turned-club secretary who visited clubs on every continent, Brother Devereux shaped the modern Order by cataloguing its scattered customs, setting shared 19th-hole principles, and in his final years urging the brotherhood to step into the digital age it now inhabits.
              </p>
           <a href="/members/brother-devereux" class="block bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all hover:border-[color:var(--accent)] no-underline">
  <!-- content -->
  <span class="text-[color:var(--accent)] hover:underline text-sm">Read Their Legend →</span>
</a>

            </div>


</div>
</section>

<!-- THE BACK NINE -->
<section class="mb-20">
<div class="text-center mb-12">
<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-[color:var(--accent)]">The Back Nine</h2>
<p class="text-xl text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-3xl mx-auto">
Those Who Carry the Tradition Forward
</p>
</div>

<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">

<!-- Member 10 -->
<div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
  <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
    <img src="/images/lady1950.png" alt="Sister Betty Parker" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
  </div>
  <div class="member-id back-nine"><span class="roman">XIX</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">398</span></div>
  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Sister Betty</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">
    Florida, USA • 1957–Present
  </p>
  <p class="text-sm mb-3 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ TPC Sawgrass</p>
  <blockquote class="text-sm italic my-4 px-3 border-l-2 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
    “We keep a club alive by inviting people in.”
  </blockquote>
  <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-4">
    A devoted mother and lifelong club member who treats every clubhouse like a second living room, Betty is the warm centre of the modern Order, pushing gently but firmly for it to step into the light.
  </p>
 <a href="/members/sister-betty" class="block bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all hover:border-[color:var(--accent)] no-underline">
  <!-- content -->
  <span class="text-[color:var(--accent)] hover:underline text-sm">Read Their Legend →</span>
</a>
</div>


<!-- Member 11 -->
<div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
  <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
    <img src="/images/man2000.png" alt="Brother Dean McLeod" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
  </div>
  <div class="member-id back-nine"><span class="roman">XIX</span><span class="separator">-</span><span class="number">451</span></div>
  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Brother Dean</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">
    St Andrews, Scotland • 1980–Present
